#Text=The Brooklyn Nets ( 15 - 16 ) defeated the Chicago Bulls ( 22 - 10 ) 96 - 82 on Tuesday at the United Center in Chicago .
#Text=The Nets used strong second and third quarters where they combined to out - score the Bulls 60 - 38 to seal the victory on the road .
#Text=They shot 43 percent from the field and 43 percent from the three - point line compared to the Bulls who shot just 38 percent from the floor and 32 percent from beyond the arc .
#Text=Free throws were also a big difference as the Nets converted on 18 - of - 21 while the Bulls only made 8 - of - 15 .

#Text=Despite questions on whether or not he would make his way back into the starting lineup , Brook Lopez eased those concerns in a big way , going 13 - for - 21 from the field to score a team - high of 29 points .
#Text=It was a good sign for Lopez , as he 's struggled to both get minutes and be productive ever since returning from injury .
#Text=Joe Johnson was also a big factor .
#Text=In 36 minutes he finished with 20 points ( 8 - 14 FG , 1 - 1 3Pt , 3 - 4 FT ) and 11 rebounds .
#Text=It was his first double - double of the year , setting a season - high for rebounds .
#Text=Deron Williams continued to come off the bench .
#Text=In 20 minutes he struggled to find his shot , going only 1 - for - 8 from the field and 0 - for - 1 from beyond the arc for six points .
#Text=Jarrett Jack and Alan Anderson had 11 points each .
#Text=For the first time in what feels like forever , Jimmy Butler seemingly struggled .
#Text=He went only 3 - for - 12 from the field and 0 - for - 3 from the three - point line to score eight points .
#Text=It was a season - low for Butler who 's only failed to reach double figures in points one other time this season .
#Text=Surprisingly , Mike Dunleavy was the Bulls highest score , as he finished with 23 points ( 9 - 15 FG , 5 - 9 3Pt ) and five rebounds .
#Text=He 's averaging only 9 points on the year , so it was a nice surprise for the Bulls .
#Text=Joakim Noah was able to record a double - double with 12 points and 12 rebounds , while Pau Gasol finished with 10 points , seven rebounds and seven assists .
#Text=The Nets ' next game will be on the road against the Orlando Magic on Friday , while the Bulls will be at home against the Denver Nuggets on Thursday .
